        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Mocksville, or 5 miles southeast of Harmony, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sheffield, Cool Springs, and Turnersburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
